briefdescription.para: Checks the configuration of the contactor-module.
Gets the latest value (TRUE, FALSE) the contactors were set to.
Reads the feedback pin of every contactor and returns its current value (CONT_SWITCH_OFF/CONT_SWITCH_ON).

detaileddescription.para: If the contactor has a feedback pin the measured feedback is returned. If the contactor has no feedback pin, it is assumed that after a certain time the contactor has reached the requested state.

briefdescription.para: Reads the feedback pins of all contactors and updates the contactors_cfg[] array with their current states.

simplesect.para: Returns E_OK if all feedbacks could be acquired (type: STD_RETURN_TYPE_e)

briefdescription.para: Sets the contactor state to its requested state, if the contactor is at that time not in the requested state.

detaileddescription.para: If the new state was already requested, but not reached (meaning the measured feedback does not return the requested state), there are two states: it can be still ok (E_OK), because the contactor has some time left to get physically in the requested state (passed time since the request is lower than the limit) or it can be not ok (E_NOT_OK), because there is timing violation, i.e. the contactor has surpassed the maximum time for getting in the requested state. It returns E_OK if the requested state was successfully set or if the contactor was at the requested state before.

briefdescription.para: Iterates over the contactor array and switches all contactors off.

simplesect.para: E_OK if all contactors were opened, E_NOT_OK if not all contactors could be opened (type: STD_RETURN_TYPE_e)

briefdescription.para: sets the current state request of the state variable cont_state.

detaileddescription.para: This function is used to make a state request to the state machine,e.g, start voltage measurement, read result of voltage measurement, re-initialization. It calls CONT_CheckStateRequest() to check if the request is valid. The state request is rejected if is not valid. The result of the check is returned immediately, so that the requester can act in case it made a non-valid state request.

simplesect.para: CONT_OK if a state request was made, CONT_STATE_NO_REQUEST if no state request was made

detaileddescription.para: This function is used in the functioning of the CONT state machine.

briefdescription.para: trigger function for the CONT driver state machine.

detaileddescription.para: This function contains the sequence of events in the CONT state machine. It must be called time-triggered, every 1ms. It exits without effect, if the function call is a reentrance.
